{"lemma": "دابِرٌ", "slug": "دابِرٌ", "root": "د.ب.ر", "root_slug": "د-ب-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/د-ب-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "دابِر", "root": "دبر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 4}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["adj"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n12015"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "past, finished", "fa": "گذشته، تمام‌شده", "ur": "گذشتہ، ختم", "tr": "geçmiş, bitmiş", "id": "masa lalu, selesai", "bn": "অতীত, শেষ", "es": "pasado, terminado", "fr": "passé, terminé", "de": "vergangen, beendet", "ru": "прошлое, завершенный", "zh": "过去的，完成的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "past, finished"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of دَبَر (dabar, “to be elapsed”)."}, "ipa": ["/daː.bir/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n12015", "headword_ar": "دَابِرٌ", "root": "dbx", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "act. part. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dabara", "text_ar": "دَبَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Following"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "behind the back; following the back; following, with respect to place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with respect to time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and also (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with respect to rank"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "station."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAbiru qawomK", "text_ar": "دَابِرُ قَوْمٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The last that remains of a people"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "party; he who comes at the end of a people"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "party;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAbiratuhumo", "text_ar": "دَابِرَتُهُمْ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; which likewise signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "those who remain after them:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAbirapN", "text_ar": "دَابِرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[so in the TA, but accord. to the T"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAbirN", "text_ar": "دَابِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which I think the right reading,] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who comes after;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "follows, another."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~alowu bayona qaAbilK wadaAbirK", "text_ar": "الدَّلْوُ بَيْنَ قَابِلٍ وَدَابِرٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The bucket is between one who advances"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with it to the well"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and one who goes back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "returns,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with it to the wateringtrough. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaEalahu daAbira A^u*unihi", "text_ar": "جَعَلَهُ دَابِرَ اُذُنِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daborN", "text_ar": "دَبْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amosi Ald~aAbiru", "text_ar": "اَمْسِ الدَّابِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almudobiru", "text_ar": "المُدْبِرُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Yesterday that is past:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K:) the epithet being here a corroborative. (S, * M.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAruwA kaA^amosi Ald~aAbiri", "text_ar": "صَارُوا كَاَمْسِ الدَّابِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They became like yesterday that is past"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hayohaAta *ahaba kamaA *ahaba A^amosi Ald~aAbiru", "text_ar": "هَيْهَاتَ ذَهَبَ كَمَا ذَهَبَ اَمْسِ الدَّابِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Far distant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is he, or it!"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, hath gone like as hath gone yesterday that is past"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also An arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that passes forth from the butt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K,) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "passes beyond it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see 1,)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and falls behind it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sahomN daAbirN", "text_ar": "سَهْمٌ دَابِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sihaAmN daAbirapN", "text_ar": "سِهَامٌ دَابِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaAbiru", "text_ar": "دَوَابِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  An arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that does not win"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the game called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almayosir", "text_ar": "المَيْسِر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAbilN", "text_ar": "قَابِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "last"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "arrow remaining in the quiver. (A.) ―         -b5-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "last"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of anything; (Ibn-Buzurj, T, M, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAbirapN", "text_ar": "دَابِرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) [see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duburN", "text_ar": "دُبُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] and (accord. to As and others, TA) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "root, stock, race,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSolN", "text_ar": "اَصْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaEa A@ll~`hu daAbirahumo", "text_ar": "قَطَعَ ا@للّٰهُ دَابِرَهُمْ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God cut off the last that remain of them."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaEa", "text_ar": "قَطَعَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hu daAbirahu", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهُ دَابِرَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God cut off the last of him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God extirpate him."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, T.) And in the Kur [vi. 45] it is said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faquTiEa daAbiru Alqawomi", "text_ar": "فَقُطِعَ دَابِرُ القَوْمِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the last of the people were extirpated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA.) And in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuqoTaEu bihi daAbiruhumo", "text_ar": "يُقْطَعُ بِهِ دَابِرُهُمْ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "All of them shall be cut off thereby, not one remaining."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b6-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dabirN", "text_ar": "دَبِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", last sentence. ―         -b7-  As an epithet applied to a camel: see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gud~apN", "text_ar": "غُدَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_r